reviewText: I have to thank the reviewers here at Amazon for turning me on to this guy. I read several reviews, enough to take a shot with this DVD and I am glad I did.Wow, this guy and his band blew me away!  This is one of the better blues concerts on DVD I have ever seen and heard. Trout, a veteran blues  singer and guitar player whom a lot of people might not know about, is solid in both departments (singing and playing.)I loved all the songs in here and really appreciated the outstanding keyboard work done by Martin Gershewitz (sp) from Cologne, Germany, a late addition to the Trout band. This guy is just great on piano/organ and Trout gives him plenty of space to work.  Also solid are bass player (James Trapp, who died recently) and the drummer.  I'm sorry didn't get all these guys names.  Each is shown their talents with solos on the final song before the customary encore.This is a pleasing sound because Trout can sing. He's not just one of the world's top blues guitarmen.  Great stuff and another good concert from this long-running  "Rockapalast" TV series in Germany.

reviewText: This is an outstanding live concert dvd of Asleep at the Wheel, Filmed on April 26, 2000, in Stuttgart, Germany. This is Alseep at the Wheel at their best. It consist of 13 great songs, and has a running time, of approximately 60 minutes. The band consists of 7 members. You get guitar players, fiddle players, drums, and a steel guitar player. Ray Benson is the lead singer & frontman.The songs are as follows:1.Cherokee Maiden2.Miles of Texas3.Route 664.Poly Poly5.Bob Wills is Still the King6.Take my Back to Tulsa7.Jumping At the Woodside8.You're from Texas9.Cherokee Boogie10.Big Balls in Cowtown11.Hot Rod Lincoln12.House of Blue Lights13.Boogie Back to TexasOverall, this is a great concert DVD, and I consider the best I've seen of Asleep at the Wheel, and therefore, I highly recommend it. Thanks!!!!
summary: Asleep at the Wheel "In Concert" = The Best Asleep at the Wheel DVD !!!!!!!!!!

reviewText: Having experienced Asleep at the Wheel about five times now, I've seen their show evolve over the years. This Ohne Filter DVD captures Asleep at the Wheel at what I would describe as their climax. Long before the introduction of the cheesy Alamo songs or  Ray Benson's corny crooner tunes, this is the best of the Asleep at the Wheel live songbook. The production is as good as it gets with the sound and video being tops. I'm with Amazon reviewer G. L. in that I was also concerned about the authenticity of a Western Swing concert recorded in Germany. One viewing ends such concerns. Unlike in the States, there are no Western hats in the audience, but the performance is the same as what the band played in Austin. Western Swing, Country, Rock and Roll, Western, Boogie-Woogie -it's all here. One of my Asleep at the Wheel live favorites has always been 'Hot Rod Lincoln.' Their studio version does the song no justice. Played live, they rock it out and I couldn't be more pleased that it made it to this disc. Recorded in Stuttgart on 4-26-00, the power of this DVD is ironic.  In the land of durndels and leiterhosen, this is the best video capture of the band that at times single handedly kept the torch of Western Swing burning brightly - swing west in Germany!
